  "why_it_matters": "Petrol = the consumer's wallet (both retailers); diesel = each group's own distribution cost. SPAR is a wholesale-distribution business, so fuel is a larger share of its cost-to-serve; it flagged 'rising fuel costs (logistics/distribution)' as an H2 FY2026 headwind. A sustained closure reverses the diesel tailwind with a lag and lifts finance costs via the SARB - hurting SPAR's net-debt position more than SHP's net-cash one."
